OL,3,CMore than 53,000 incidents of drivers
OL,4,Cignoring smart motorway lane closed
OL,5,Csigns
OL,7,FMore than 53,000 incidents of drivers
OL,8,Fignoring lane closed signs on smart
OL,9,Fmotorways have been recorded since
OL,10,F2021, according to new research.
OL,12,FRoad safety charity IAM RoadSmart,
OL,13,Fwhich conducted the study, said it
OL,14,Fdemonstrates the Government must give
OL,15,F"serious thought" about the future of
OL,16,Fthe roads.
OL,18,FAdherence to red X signs is critical
OL,19,Fto safety on smart motorways which had
OL,20,Ftheir hard shoulder converted into a
OL,21,Flive running lane.
